<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="rtpcr">rtPCR</a> - Reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction (see <a href="#polymerase_chain_reaction_pcr">PCR</a>), this technique uses a special form of <a href="#polymerase">polymerase</a> to reverse the <a href="#transcription">transcription</a> process. This allows for us to go from a sample of <a href="#rna">RNA</a> to the associated <a href="#rna">DNA</a>.